-- Introduction --

This directory should contain the IBM decNumber library.  decNumber can be
downloaded for free at:

       http://www.alphaworks.ibm.com/tech/decnumber

The source should be compiled to two files named 'LINUXDecNum.a' and
'LINUXDecFloats.a', then either copied or linked in each benchmark's directory.
We have included a Makefile that will compile the library correctly.


-- Compilation --

To compile, please download all source files into this directory. We have provided
a Makefile that archives and names the library to what the benchmarks expect.

To make the library type:

make clean
make


-- <DEC_DATATYPE> Support --

The decNumber library provides support for the following <DEC_DATATYPE> options:

   (1) DECNUMBER_ARBITRARY - arbitrary precision decNumber library
   (2) DECNUMBER_FIXED - fixed precision decNumber library
